id: pm-5u9z
title: Suppress benign extension_service_override_collision when calendar+guide-shell both bundled
description: "In any project with `pm init --with-packages` (or after bundled packages are installed), `pm health` reports a warning: `extension_service_override_collision:output_format:project:builtin-guide-shell:project:builtin-calendar`. Both built-in packages register an `output_format` service; the loader already chains them deterministically (pm-rnpb feature note: `chain output_format service overrides for package renderers`). Demote this expected configuration to debug-level or silence it when the chained loader resolved without ambiguity. Currently fires `ok=true` but produces alarming warning text on every health run."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 2
tags[4]: agent-ux,extensions,health,pm-cli
created_at: "2026-05-17T19:19:37.251Z"
updated_at: "2026-05-17T19:45:34.155Z"
author: claude-code-agent
acceptance_criteria: Default `pm init --with-packages` + `pm health` produces no warnings; collision still flagged for non-builtin conflicts; regression test added
parent: pm-rnpb
resolution: Classified output_format service overrides as chained registrations so expected bundled package renderers do not emit collision warnings.
expected_result: pm init --with-packages followed by pm health has no benign output_format collision warning while non-chained service collisions still warn.
actual_result: "Extension-loader regression, isolated dogfood, semantic dogfood, and release gates verified the behavior."
